s and historic norms stocks purchased also typically operate in outoffavor industries in terms of performance valuation and sentiment acceptable financial leverage and strong cash flow and revenue per share alongside earnings improvement potential are additional common attributes of purchases stocks are typically sold when no longer undervalued or no longer out of favor we deploy capital for the longterm beyond wall street’s typical  month horizon seeking an adequate absolute return in a tax efficient manner owning quality businesses for the longterm ie  years makes for good aftertax results we invest where a reasonable starting valuation allows business cash flows not perceptions to ultimately drive investment results key attributes associated with the firm’s opportunistic value equity strategy  opportunistic investment across the full range of market capitalization  portfolios concentrated among  to  stocks  portfolio construction without regard to any benchmark  sector weightings are residual of stock selection  owning cash as a defensive tool  emphasis on aftertax returns where relevant quarterly commentaries nd quarter  view more portfolio manager interviews winter 8 april th 8 december th  copyright   knightsbridge asset management llc · powered by wordpress lightword theme by andrei luca go to top ↑ professionals  knightsbridge asset management llc knightsbridge asset management llc phone    email knightsbridgeknightsbcom home philosophy investing professionals quarterly commentaries contact us professionals investment team john g prichard cfa john g prichard cfa cofounder  principal president a cofounder of knightsbridge john serves as the chief investment officer and president  he has  years of investment experience prior to the  cofounding of knightsbridge john worked at canterbury capital services inc and in the investment department of santa barbara bank and trust he earned an ma in finance and banking from boston university and a ba in economics from th